Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 12:30:02 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 1/5] feat(agentic): wire grounded observations into live
 inspection
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Makes Eyes V2 + inspection replay REACHABLE from the real inspection entrypoint (inspectAndPlan, the
function the inspection job runs), not just a demo.

  - Eyes V2 was already produced in the live pipeline (P1 put deriveObservations in buildProductMap,
    which inspectAndPlan calls); this adds a production-path integration test proving it: a real
    inspectAndPlan run yields map.observations with SEEN facts + transitions and a stable
    observationSetDigest (= map.observations.digest), carried in the existing inspection_jobs.result
    JSON. The digest is digest-neutral (map.digest unchanged whether observations are present).
  - Wires runReplayShadow into inspectAndPlan AFTER the map is built, behind INSPECTION_REPLAY_MODE=
    off|shadow (default off → the whole block is a no-op, artifact byte-identical). In shadow it
    re-performs a safe observed transition through the C4 guarded egress proxy and attaches a LEAK-SAFE
    ReplayShadowRecordV1 (result codes + transition ids + digests only) to map.replayShadow. It NEVER
    affects payout or mission acceptance, and a replay failure never fails the inspection (fully caught).
  - runReplayShadow now returns leak-safe per-probe records; an additive opts.replayDeps lets a test
    inject the egress allowlist for a local fixture (production passes nothing → the proxy blocks
    loopback as it must).

Production-path tests (through inspectAndPlan, only external effects mocked): Eyes V2 facts + stable
digest with replay OFF (no browser); digest carried without shifting map.digest; legacy inspection (no
field test) still plans; shadow with an unreachable target records honestly (never a synthetic
"reproduced"). Plus one GATED real-browser inspection (`npm run test:inspection-live`) that runs the
REAL pipeline against a local fixture and reproduces the observed click→state transition.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
