Subject: [PATCH 2/5] feat(agentic): wire observation judgment v2 into payout
 shadow
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Makes Observation Judge V2 REACHABLE from the real payout pipeline (runDeputyOnSubmission's observation
lane), threaded through the EXISTING private-corpus seam — no second corpus, no DB migration, no change
to the legacy corpus or the money outcome.

  - reconstructSetFromCorpus() rebuilds a minimal observation set from the campaign's existing
    privateCorpus ({source,text}[]) at judge time — READ-ONLY: seen state/page facts, distinct source =
    distinct stateId. The flat corpus has no transitions, so V2 runs in its state-specific mode; V2 is
    made robust to a transition-less set (the state-specific + no-contradiction bar still discriminates a
    generic account from a genuine one, since state-specificity is the discriminator).
  - observationV2Shadow() runs V2 on the submission's account + the reconstructed corpus, compares to the
    legacy bar, and returns a LEAK-SAFE record (disagreement class, counts, digests, reason codes — never
    corpus text), plus a multilingual_corroboration_missing flag (a real recall limit, never auto-passed).
  - Wired into the observation lane behind OBS_JUDGE_V2_MODE=off|shadow (default off). In shadow it adds a
    `v2` key to the observationShadow journal + an agent-log line; it NEVER touches `autopay` or settlement.

Production-path tests (through the real runDeputyOnSubmission): mode off → no v2 attached; shadow → v2
journaled and settlement UNCHANGED (still held, autopay off); a generic account with a passing legacy
bar → v2_stricter, journaled with no corpus text leaked. The full action→outcome V2 (with transitions)
needs the observation set persisted on the campaign — a follow-up that would require a new field; this
sprint keeps to the existing seam.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
