MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Makes the resumable TaskRunV1 controller REACHABLE from the real runConcierge loop (shadow-observer),
behind CONCIERGE_TASK_RUN_MODE=off|shadow (default off; "enforce" reserved + not honored). Off mode is
byte-identical (shadow is null → the legacy array is persisted and no observe/advance runs).

  - concierge-shadow.ts: conciergeTaskRunMode(); extractIntent() (URL + budget from the founder message);
    mapConciergeTool() maps a concierge tool + its JSON result to a controller ToolOutcome, extracting
    AUTHORITATIVE ids ONLY from the tool result (sage_start_inspection→inspect, sage_get_inspection→
    poll_inspection, sage_fund_and_launch→fund_and_launch with overCap/needsFunding/needsGas); a
    non-lifecycle tool maps to null so its text can never set an id. ConciergeTaskShadow observes each
    real tool result, advances the controller, and can persist/resume a backward-compatible V2 envelope.
  - Wired into runConciergeTurn: in shadow mode it reads the memory envelope, resumes or starts a
    TaskRunV1, advances it from each REAL tool result in the loop, honors an approval message at the
    awaiting_approval boundary, and persists the V2 envelope (readMemory upgrades a legacy array). The
    authoritative loop, tool execution, reply, ids, approval, and money are unchanged.

Tests (7, no LLM/network): mode gating; tool→outcome mapping with ids from tools only; intent extraction;
a full observed turn (intake→inspect→poll→stop at approval); a fabricated id in non-lifecycle tool text
is ignored; RESUME across a restart via the V2 envelope (fund id from the tool → active); a hard fund
failure blocks (no blind retry). The controller's 8-scenario safety is already proven in task-run.test;
this proves the shadow observes the REAL loop correctly. A full end-to-end runConcierge trial with fake
models is deferred to the S6 runtime demo.

