Root-causes the P-ENTAIL 0/15 and fixes it. The old live harness ADAPTED the payout judge fixtures —
giving only criterion 0 a blind 60-char evidence slice as its quote and leaving every other criterion's
quote null — so it sent malformed multi-criterion inputs the entailment checker could not verify, and
every model output failed the strict per-criterion validation (invalid_output). The 0/15 was a HARNESS
defect, NOT a model-quality result.

  - entailment-fixtures.ts: a purpose-built corpus — 13 SINGLE-criterion fixtures, each with a VERBATIM
    quote of its bounded evidence (enforced at module load) and the verdict a correct checker must return,
    tagged by trap: direct entailment, partial satisfaction, quote-supports-wrong-criterion, generic
    quote, negation, numeric/actor/temporal mismatch, stale state, adjacent-nonsupporting, multilingual
    entailment + non-entailment, injection-in-context.
  - promotion-eval.live.test.ts now drives P-ENTAIL from this corpus (one criterion + one real quote per
    call) and reports the verdict vs expected by trap.
  - entailment-corpus.test.ts (21, deterministic, fake provider): every quote is verbatim; a correct
    verdict vetoes each non-entailing trap and clears each entailing one; and the veto FAILS CLOSED
    (vetoes) on missing/duplicate/wrong-id results, a bad verdict enum, fenced/prose output, truncation,
    and an absent finish_reason. The frozen entailment veto logic is unchanged (entailment.test green).

A LIVE P-ENTAIL over this corpus is owed when CommonStack quota is unthrottled (currently 429).

